10 km by gravel road SE of San José and the turnoff from the Santa Cruz- Samaipata highway. Extensive area of unconsolidated sediments just E of the true rocky Andes mountains, with the ridge tops all at the same level (ca. 700 m), deeply and finely eroded into hills and narrow valleys. Dry forest on top of hills and upper slopes, with Acacia polyphylla, Caesalpinia pluviosa, Attelea phalerata, Trichilia claussenii, Aspidosperma cylindrocarpum, Helicteres lhotskyana.
